<section id="about">
  <h2>About the project</h2>
  <p style="color:var(--muted);max-width:900px">This project focuses on a lightweight, modular aquatic drone equipped with high-resolution cameras, multispectral lighting, and environmental sensors. The drone performs low-impact surveys to study fish populations, coral health, algal blooms and invasive organisms. Data is annotated with geotags and timecodes for later analysis using machine learning models.</p>

  <div class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="card"><strong>Autonomy</strong><p style="color:var(--muted);margin:8px 0 0">Waypoint navigation, obstacle avoidance and adaptive transects.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><strong>Imaging</strong><p style="color:var(--muted);margin:8px 0 0">High-frame-rate cameras + multispectral lights for organism ID and health assessment.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><strong>Cloud analysis</strong><p style="color:var(--muted);margin:8px 0 0">Secure upload and automated annotation pipelines for ML training.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

